                <head>434. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>President <persName corresp="#p_NDD1">Ngo Dinh Diem</persName> of the Republic of
                    Vietnam visited the United States for 21 days in May 1957. As part of his
                    official discussions with United States officials in Washington, he met with
                        <persName>Dulles</persName> and others on May 9. The situation in Laos was
                    one of the topics of discussion. For a record of that conversation, see the
                    memorandum of conversation, May 9, <ref target="frus1955-57v01#pg_801">volume I,
                        page 801</ref>.</p>
            </div>
